Tamil Nadu
Dec 12, 2014
Murder
Description:
			A man was today arrested on charges of murdering a 20-year-old girl by slashing her neck with a knife after she spurned his offer to marry, police here said.

The 24-year-old Eswaran used to pester the girl, a relative, to marry him but she refused as he was unemployed, police said.

Irked over this, Eswaran entered her house at Usilampatti in the district this afternoon when she was alone and slashed her neck with a knife leading to her instantaneous death, police said.

He was arrested under IPC section 302 for murder, they said.

